Name
    ngx_recaptcha_access_filter_module

Description
    This is a nginx module that reads HTTP POST request body encoded
    in "application/x-www-form-urlencoded", lookup for arguments:
	
		recaptcha_challenge_field
		recaptcha_response_field

	and if they are present perform the reCAPTCHA validation.

	Parse the Google reCAPTCHA validation responseand return 403 
	if varification fail; otherwise goes on. 	
	
    You can check the validation process here:

		(http://code.google.com/apis/recaptcha/docs/verify.html)

	This module require libCurl (http://curl.haxx.se/download.html).

Installation
        Be sure to have installed libCurl; the module require it to
        connect with Google reCAPTCHA verify service.
 
        Get the nginx source code from nginx.net (http://nginx.org/).
        Unpack the source code and build nginx with this module.

        $ wget 'http://nginx.org/download/nginx-0.8.54.tar.gz'
        $ tar -xzvf nginx-0.8.54.tar.gz
        $ cd nginx-0.8.54.tar.gz/

        $ git-clone git@github.com:Lus71/ngx_recaptcha_access_filter_module.git

        $ ./configure --add-module=/somepath/ngx_recaptcha_access_filter_module
        $ make -j2
        $ make install

Usage
        recaptcha on;
        recaptcha_private_key "YOUR GOOGLE reCAPTCHA PRIVATE KEY";

    example:

        #nginx.conf

        location /register {
            recaptcha on;
            recaptcha_private_key "YOUR GOOGLE reCAPTCHA PRIVATE KEY";
            proxy_pass http://backends
        }
 

